  "origins": [
    {
      "id": 12591,
      "title": "Dietary choices of Brits",
      "description": "This dataset contains the result of semiannual YouGov surveys of around 2,000 adults aged 18 years and older in the UK, asking the question: \"Which of these best describes your diet?\". The available responses were:\n- Meat eater: eat meat and/or poultry.\n- Flexitarian: mainly vegetarian, but occasionally eat meat or fish.\n- Pescetarian: eat fish but do not eat meat or poultry.\n- Vegetarian: do not eat any meat, poultry, game, fish, or shellfish.\n- Plant-based / Vegan: do not eat dairy products, eggs, or any other animal product.\n- None of these.",
